<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1148,2039]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,495,1868,1894]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—Until now, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[869,1143,1868,1894]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">
<emphasis box="[869,1143,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">Passiflora caparaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be restricted to PNC (
<figureCitation box="[207,276,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[136,229,855,877]" captionTargetBox="[352,1236,203,818]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[340,1247,190,831]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Geographical distribution map of Passiflora caparaoensis and P. campanulata. BA= Bahia, ES= Espírito Santo, GO= Goiás, MT= Mato Grosso, MS= Mato Grosso do Sul, MG= Minas Gerais, PR= Paraná, RJ= Rio de Janeiro, RS= Rio Grande do Sul, SC= Santa Catarina, SP= São Paulo." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534633/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, blue dots). This known population occurs at an elevation of approximately 
<quantity box="[1146,1348,1904,1931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0949999999999998" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.9899999999999998" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" unit="m" value="2095.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="1990.0">1,990 to 2,200 m</quantity>
.a.s.l. in a cloud forest, in the transition area between high montane ombrophilous forest and high-altitude grassland, near the riverbed. In this environment, temperatures can be extremely low throughout the year (reaching ca. min 4ºC) (ICMBio 2015).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
