<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,1965,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1965,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The name of the new species refers to the location of its record, known as the region of Caparaó, between 
<collectingRegion box="[236,386,2001,2027]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[441,601,2001,2027]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
states, and that gives the name to Caparaó National Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
