<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="143" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1396,2034]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,323,1396,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Phenology:</emphasis>
—This species was collected with buds, flowers and fruits in January and with flowers in September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="143" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1396,2034]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,438,1467,1494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—Critically Endangered (CR). The observed population of 
<taxonomicName box="[1119,1298,1469,1494]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">
<emphasis box="[1119,1298,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">P. caparaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains less than ten mature individuals. In its occurrence area, we found the presence of an invasive species of fern, 
<taxonomicName class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Pteridium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquilinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Pteridium aquilinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Kunth (1879: 11), and a continuous flow of tourists. At present, we are not aware of any other locality where this species persists. Therefore, we suggest that the species can be categorized as CR, considering the very small or restricted population with less than 50 individuals (criterion D) (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[887,1025,1612,1638]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" refId="ref6456" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2022) Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 15. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 116 pp. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 24 April 2022)" type="book" year="2022">IUCN 2022</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
